                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Through the Brazilian minister at London and the British minister here, the
                    Government is informally advised of a proposal coming from Great Britain to
                    arbitrate Trinidad question. The President has the question under consideration.
                    Minister for foreign affairs’ legal opinion against it, but considerations of
                    policy may induce an acceptance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thompson</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
